Plotly/ECharts plot
7. Smart Lazy Loading (Critical)

Load data only when needed.

Example:

observeEvent(input$zoom_range,{
   data <- query_subset(input$zoom_range)
   plot(data)
})

So zooming re-queries the database instead of plotting everything.

8. Best Storage Formats

Avoid CSV for large datasets.

Use:

Format	Why
Parquet	fastest
Feather	fast
DuckDB	SQL queries
HDF5	scientific data

Example:

write_parquet(data,"dataset.parquet")
